      "Walk into a meeting alongside two professionals, one with five years of experience and one with twenty-five, and they will not see the same room. The less experienced person will follow the agenda, listen to the arguments, and take note of what is said. The veteran will register something else entirely: the hesitation before a direct question is answered, the shift in posture when a particular topic arises, the fact that someone who usually speaks early has gone quiet. Before a single substantive point has been debated, the experienced practitioner has already begun to form a reading of the situation that the newer colleague has no access to.",
