      "Timing is one of the earliest things experienced practitioners learn to notice. Not just the timing of markets or product cycles, but the smaller, more human varieties. When is a person ready to hear difficult feedback? When has a conflict matured to the point where intervention will help rather than harden positions? When is a silence in a conversation productive, and when does it signal that something important is being withheld? These are not questions that can be answered by policy. They require a feel for the texture of a moment, and that feel is built from having misjudged the timing often enough to recognize when it is right.",
