      "Judgment, in most professional fields, is treated as something a person either has or lacks. It is praised in annual reviews, cited in promotions, and invoked whenever an organization needs to explain why one leader succeeded where another did not. But for all the weight the word carries, remarkably little attention is paid to how judgment actually forms. It is spoken of as a trait rather than a structure, as though it arrived whole rather than being assembled over time.",
