      "This is one of the less examined gaps in professional life. People who are genuinely skilled at what they do are not always able to describe how they do it. A surgeon knows when something about a procedure feels wrong before the data confirms it. A portfolio manager recognizes the early signals of a market shift without being able to list the indicators in sequence. A school superintendent senses when a policy will meet resistance before it is announced. The knowing is real. The explanation lags behind.",
